1
00:00:20,176 --> 00:00:23,446
I'm begging you for forgiveness.

2
00:00:23,446 --> 00:00:29,519
Please forgive my good-for-nothing daughter this time.

3
00:00:29,519 --> 00:00:31,621
For my sake,
just this time.

4
00:01:06,889 --> 00:01:08,992
Oppa.

5
00:01:12,028 --> 00:01:14,831
Why did you come out? 
Not sleeping yet?

6
00:01:14,831 --> 00:01:16,933
I woke up.

7
00:01:17,166 --> 00:01:20,436
You were not there.
Why?

8
00:01:20,670 --> 00:01:22,305
It's nothing.

9
00:01:22,305 --> 00:01:24,641
Is something bothering you?

10
00:01:24,641 --> 00:01:29,078
I'm a little busy with work.
Go in.

11
00:02:04,347 --> 00:02:06,215
Husband.

12
00:02:08,318 --> 00:02:10,887
What?
Do you need anything?

13
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:16,726
What happened to you? 
Why do you moan when evening comes?

14
00:02:16,726 --> 00:02:17,894
Me?

15
00:02:17,894 --> 00:02:23,266
You just sit in front of the table once you get to school.
What's so tiring about that?

16
00:02:23,266 --> 00:02:26,302
It's a little tiring.

17
00:02:26,302 --> 00:02:28,171
Water please.

18
00:02:34,477 --> 00:02:36,813
What's wrong with your hand?

19
00:02:36,813 --> 00:02:40,783
Let me see.
Why is your hand like a labourer's?

20
00:02:41,017 --> 00:02:43,820
I hurt it in school.

21
00:02:44,053 --> 00:02:48,257
I don't know about the rest but
your hands are prettier than mine.

22
00:02:48,257 --> 00:02:50,593
Pretty hands for men?

23
00:02:50,593 --> 00:02:53,863
Just go to sleep.
Let's not talk about my hands.

24
00:02:53,863 --> 00:02:56,666
I should feel sleepy first.

25
00:02:56,666 --> 00:03:00,637
I have a load of worries.

26
00:03:00,870 --> 00:03:04,607
What's going to happen to Su Bak?

27
00:03:11,147 --> 00:03:15,585
Once I apply this,
my mouth opens at once.

28
00:03:15,585 --> 00:03:17,687
It's really amazing to watch you 
apply make-up.

29
00:03:17,687 --> 00:03:20,957
I used to be famous for my make-up.

30
00:03:20,957 --> 00:03:22,825
My mom is starting to lie again?

31
00:03:22,825 --> 00:03:29,599
- This kid.
- Mother, I'm going.
- Okay, take care.

32
00:03:30,767 --> 00:03:31,467
Yes.

33
00:03:31,701 --> 00:03:33,336
I'll go with you.

34
00:03:33,336 --> 00:03:34,971
I'm going to work starting today.

35
00:03:34,971 --> 00:03:37,540
You're pregnant.
Is it okay?

36
00:03:37,540 --> 00:03:40,109
She said it's better than staying at home,
so I agreed.

37
00:03:45,014 --> 00:03:48,751
Father, goodbye.

38
00:03:54,123 --> 00:03:56,225
I'm also going to work from now on.

39
00:03:56,459 --> 00:03:59,495
Do you want me to do something for you
before I go to work?

40
00:03:59,495 --> 00:04:01,831
Never mind.

41
00:04:09,772 --> 00:04:11,174
Are you going somewhere?

42
00:04:11,174 --> 00:04:14,677
I am meeting someone.
Look after the shop.

43
00:04:14,677 --> 00:04:17,013
Su Bak is doing well?

44
00:04:17,013 --> 00:04:20,750
I think she was reprimanded by Ajubeonim.
She's listless.

45
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:23,319
Su Bak is the black sheep of that family.

46
00:04:23,319 --> 00:04:25,188
Her family got bankrupt because of her.

47
00:04:25,188 --> 00:04:28,691
I feel bad for her.
Everyone's ignoring her.

48
00:04:28,691 --> 00:04:30,793
Her husband left her.

49
00:04:30,793 --> 00:04:33,129
She got what she deserved.

50
00:04:33,363 --> 00:04:35,231
I would never do that.

51
00:04:35,231 --> 00:04:37,567
Oppa is the only man for me till I die.

52
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:40,603
Right, Wang Dal?

53
00:04:47,143 --> 00:04:49,479
Mom.

54
00:04:50,179 --> 00:04:54,150
You're an enemy.
An enemy.

55
00:04:54,150 --> 00:04:56,019
It's all your fault.

56
00:04:56,019 --> 00:04:59,289
No one else knew aside from you.

57
00:04:59,289 --> 00:05:01,858
I told you it wasn't me.
Why don't you believe me?

58
00:05:01,858 --> 00:05:04,894
You should have stopped your sister 
from having an affair.

59
00:05:04,894 --> 00:05:07,697
I tried.
I tried to stop her but she wouldn't listen.

60
00:05:07,697 --> 00:05:10,967
You should have told me.

61
00:05:10,967 --> 00:05:14,470
If you couldn't stop her,
you should have kept it a secret till the end.

62
00:05:14,470 --> 00:05:17,974
You told him everything and made her divorce.

63
00:05:17,974 --> 00:05:19,375
Whose side are you on?

64
00:05:19,375 --> 00:05:21,944
Your brother-in-law's or your sister's?

65
00:05:22,178 --> 00:05:26,849
I want to be on Brother-in-law's side 
but blood is thicker than water so 
I have no choice but to be on Eonni's side.

66
00:05:28,718 --> 00:05:29,419
I hate him too.

67
00:05:29,419 --> 00:05:33,856
I don't believe whatever you say.

68
00:05:33,856 --> 00:05:39,696
I'm already sick like this, you should ask for 
a leave of absence and take care of me.

69
00:05:39,929 --> 00:05:42,966
How despicable.
Get out!
I don't want to see you.

70
00:05:42,966 --> 00:05:45,535
Why do you get angry at me 
the moment you see me?

71
00:05:45,535 --> 00:05:47,403
I won't come again.
Take care of yourself.

72
00:05:47,403 --> 00:05:49,505
You...
Hey!

73
00:05:53,009 --> 00:05:56,746
Hey! Let's talk.

74
00:05:56,746 --> 00:05:58,147
Oh my.
I'm so tired.

75
00:05:58,147 --> 00:06:00,950
I'm talking to you.
Why won't you answer me?

76
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:05,388
Hey, please come out for a moment.

77
00:06:05,388 --> 00:06:07,724
Please come out for a moment.

78
00:06:07,724 --> 00:06:09,826
Hey, Mr. Security Guard.

79
00:06:09,826 --> 00:06:14,964
I will take the boxes here, okay?

80
00:06:14,964 --> 00:06:18,001
Oh.
The back of his head looks like my son's.

81
00:06:18,234 --> 00:06:21,971
My son is the head teacher of the school over there.

82
00:06:21,971 --> 00:06:26,643
He's a head teacher the whole neighbourhood respects.

83
00:06:26,876 --> 00:06:36,452
Thank you.
Oh.

84
00:06:36,686 --> 00:06:41,357
Oh, oh.
Thank you. Thank you.

85
00:06:41,357 --> 00:06:44,627
I got a lot.

86
00:06:48,364 --> 00:06:50,466
Why?

87
00:06:50,466 --> 00:06:55,605
You can't even differentiate a rag from a towel?

88
00:06:56,773 --> 00:07:01,678
Turn my body.
I'll get bedsores.

89
00:07:02,845 --> 00:07:05,415
How?

90
00:07:07,517 --> 00:07:13,122
Turn my body around.
Let my back lean on the pillow.

91
00:07:14,991 --> 00:07:15,458
It's cold.

92
00:07:15,458 --> 00:07:18,261
Stupid fool.

93
00:07:18,494 --> 00:07:20,830
You don't even know how to do that?

94
00:07:20,830 --> 00:07:24,334
What exactly do you know?

95
00:07:24,334 --> 00:07:26,669
I'm going crazy.

96
00:07:26,669 --> 00:07:29,238
What should I do?

97
00:07:29,472 --> 00:07:33,676
You bankrupted our family,
had an affair and got a divorce.

98
00:07:33,676 --> 00:07:36,245
You make my blood boil.

99
00:07:36,479 --> 00:07:38,348
I can't live because of you!

100
00:07:38,348 --> 00:07:42,085
Oh.
Do you know how to do anything at all?

101
00:07:42,085 --> 00:07:46,990
Do you know how to feed your child
or take care of your sick mom?

102
00:07:46,990 --> 00:07:48,858
What do you want me to do?

103
00:07:48,858 --> 00:07:50,960
Do you think it's easy for me to accommodate you?

104
00:07:51,194 --> 00:07:53,062
Please stop!

105
00:07:53,062 --> 00:07:58,434
You keep nagging.
I want to die too.

106
00:08:02,872 --> 00:08:06,142
That brat doesn't even know how to do this.

107
00:08:27,163 --> 00:08:30,667
Manager, you're not going to your parents' place?

108
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:32,302
No.

109
00:08:32,302 --> 00:08:36,739
You even asked for a leave of absence
because your mom can't move.

110
00:08:36,739 --> 00:08:39,309
Did something happen?

111
00:08:39,309 --> 00:08:42,111
She'll still be okay without me.

112
00:08:42,812 --> 00:08:44,447
This is heavy, don't carry it.

113
00:08:44,447 --> 00:08:47,016
I got a call earlier and he said
you must not carry heavy stuff.

114
00:08:47,016 --> 00:08:49,585
He told me again and again.

115
00:08:49,585 --> 00:08:51,688
Who?
Sin Dong dad?

116
00:08:51,688 --> 00:08:54,724
Yes. 
He said, you should be careful.

117
00:08:59,162 --> 00:09:02,198
Han Na. 
I'll be back in a moment.

118
00:09:02,432 --> 00:09:05,234
Okay, you'll feel better that way.

119
00:09:05,234 --> 00:09:05,935
Take this.

120
00:09:06,169 --> 00:09:07,804
Oh!

121
00:09:08,738 --> 00:09:12,709
Mom, I bought some roast sweet potato.

122
00:09:12,942 --> 00:09:14,344
Bad girl.

123
00:09:14,344 --> 00:09:15,278
What are you doing here?

124
00:09:15,278 --> 00:09:16,446
Go.

125
00:09:16,446 --> 00:09:19,949
Children are useless. 

126
00:09:20,416 --> 00:09:22,518
What happened here?

127
00:09:22,518 --> 00:09:25,555
Where is Eonni?

128
00:09:25,788 --> 00:09:32,562
I said a few words to her then 
she stalked off leaving everything behind.

129
00:09:32,795 --> 00:09:36,532
I really want to die.

130
00:09:37,467 --> 00:09:40,269
Geez.
The blanket's all wet.

131
00:09:40,269 --> 00:09:44,007
How could she leave?

132
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:48,911
Mom, staying here all the time
is hard and frustrating.

133
00:09:48,911 --> 00:09:51,247
But what can you do?

134
00:09:51,247 --> 00:09:54,984
You'll only get frustrated
if you get mad.

135
00:09:54,984 --> 00:09:57,086
Don't say anything to Eonni.

136
00:09:57,086 --> 00:10:02,692
It already happened.
The one who's most upset now is Eonni.

137
00:10:02,692 --> 00:10:07,130
Mom, let me change the blankets.

138
00:10:30,253 --> 00:10:30,720
What?

139
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,121
Where are you?

140
00:10:32,121 --> 00:10:32,822
Mom's home.

141
00:10:32,822 --> 00:10:36,326
Again?
If something happens to you,
you'll get it from me.

142
00:10:36,326 --> 00:10:37,727
Okay, bye.

143
00:10:37,727 --> 00:10:40,530
Hello? Sin Dong mom.

144
00:10:40,530 --> 00:10:43,333
I'm really going crazy.

145
00:10:49,172 --> 00:10:50,807
Ho Bak.

146
00:10:50,807 --> 00:10:52,909
Wait a moment.

147
00:10:53,843 --> 00:10:55,945
What's wrong?

148
00:10:55,945 --> 00:11:00,149
What to do? 
I think I have diarrhoea.

149
00:11:00,149 --> 00:11:02,018
What's going on?

150
00:11:02,485 --> 00:11:03,653
It's okay.

151
00:11:03,886 --> 00:11:06,222
Since you have to go,
don't feel sorry.

152
00:11:06,222 --> 00:11:08,091
I'll get water.

153
00:11:12,528 --> 00:11:14,397
Get up.

154
00:11:14,397 --> 00:11:14,864
What are you doing here?

155
00:11:14,864 --> 00:11:16,032
I said get up.

156
00:11:16,032 --> 00:11:18,368
Really. Be quiet. 
Quiet.

157
00:11:18,368 --> 00:11:20,003
Geez.

158
00:11:20,003 --> 00:11:22,105
Don't.

159
00:11:22,105 --> 00:11:24,907
Tell them.
Tell--

160
00:11:29,345 --> 00:11:30,513
What's wrong with you?

161
00:11:30,747 --> 00:11:32,615
Is this helping me?

162
00:11:32,615 --> 00:11:35,652
Does this make sense?
The doctor told you to be careful.

163
00:11:35,885 --> 00:11:37,987
The doctor said it's okay.

164
00:11:37,987 --> 00:11:39,622
Where is Sister-in-law?
Why can't I see her?

165
00:11:39,622 --> 00:11:41,491
Is she having fun outside?

166
00:11:41,491 --> 00:11:45,461
She's not.
She fought with Mom.

167
00:11:45,461 --> 00:11:49,666
Well done.
Now, she knows who's truly her daughter.

168
00:11:49,666 --> 00:11:51,534
Does she really know?

169
00:11:51,534 --> 00:11:54,804
Don't do that.
Let me feel comfortable.

170
00:11:54,804 --> 00:11:57,607
Compared to a comfortable body,
having a clear conscience is better.

171
00:11:57,607 --> 00:12:00,410
I won't be at ease if I lie down quietly.

172
00:12:00,643 --> 00:12:02,979
Since it has already happened,
be quiet.

173
00:12:02,979 --> 00:12:05,081
Just for 2 weeks.

174
00:12:05,081 --> 00:12:07,417
I just can't understand your family.

175
00:12:07,417 --> 00:12:09,052
Your idle sister should do this.

176
00:12:09,052 --> 00:12:13,723
Asking a pregnant person to come here and wipe ass.
Does it make sense?

177
00:12:13,957 --> 00:12:18,628
Stop nagging.
Go home and prepare food.
Do you understand?

178
00:12:19,329 --> 00:12:20,496
I'm really going crazy.

179
00:12:43,386 --> 00:12:48,524
I used to be afraid of marriage.
But now that I met you,
I want to get married as soon as possible.

180
00:12:48,524 --> 00:12:49,926
When is good time for you?

181
00:12:49,926 --> 00:12:53,429
Give me some time. 
I have adult children.

182
00:12:53,663 --> 00:12:56,232
I can't just do what I want.

183
00:12:56,232 --> 00:12:58,801
Your children are opposing?

184
00:12:58,801 --> 00:13:03,239
I've been alone for so long.
The children will be surpirsed.

185
00:13:03,473 --> 00:13:11,180
I didn't date any men.
I was quite a straight shooter.

186
00:13:13,049 --> 00:13:15,385
Wait.

187
00:13:20,523 --> 00:13:22,392
Is it warm?

188
00:13:22,625 --> 00:13:25,194
Yes, it's warm.

189
00:13:25,194 --> 00:13:31,267
Looking at you like this,
you come off as a bit of a player.

190
00:13:32,201 --> 00:13:36,406
I don't do this for anyone.
This is only forever for you.

191
00:13:36,406 --> 00:13:45,281
It's warm like this. After we get married,
you can also put your feet here.

192
00:13:53,923 --> 00:13:56,259
What's wrong?

193
00:13:56,259 --> 00:13:57,894
I want to carry you.

194
00:13:58,127 --> 00:14:00,697
Your leg must hurt from all the walking.

195
00:14:00,697 --> 00:14:03,032
It's all right.

196
00:14:03,032 --> 00:14:05,601
Hop on.
Hurry.
Come.

197
00:14:05,601 --> 00:14:08,171
Come.

198
00:14:14,243 --> 00:14:17,513
Oh my god.

199
00:14:25,688 --> 00:14:26,155
Wait a moment.

200
00:14:26,155 --> 00:14:28,958
Nice.

201
00:14:31,294 --> 00:14:33,630
Put me down.

202
00:14:33,630 --> 00:14:35,498
What?

203
00:14:35,498 --> 00:14:40,169
Se Dal.

204
00:14:42,271 --> 00:14:44,140
What's wrong?

205
00:14:45,541 --> 00:14:48,111
Sa--

206
00:15:01,658 --> 00:15:07,030
Talk to Mom.

207
00:15:07,030 --> 00:15:08,665
I have nothing to say. I told you...
Once you get cheated, you'll get cheated again.

208
00:15:08,665 --> 00:15:10,300
He's not like that.

209
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:14,037
He's really a nice person.
Meet him.

210
00:15:16,372 --> 00:15:18,474
When did you start dating?

211
00:15:18,474 --> 00:15:21,744
Roughly two months.

212
00:15:21,744 --> 00:15:23,146
Two months?

213
00:15:23,146 --> 00:15:24,547
It's just 2 months,

214
00:15:24,547 --> 00:15:26,182
and you say that punk is a good man.

215
00:15:26,182 --> 00:15:28,284
Don't call him punk.

216
00:15:28,284 --> 00:15:30,153
He's not someone you should call punk.

217
00:15:30,153 --> 00:15:32,488
I don't want to talk to you.

218
00:15:50,940 --> 00:15:53,977
Yeong Dal is also married.

219
00:15:53,977 --> 00:15:57,947
I feel so lonely and empty.

220
00:15:57,947 --> 00:15:59,582
I'm here.

221
00:15:59,582 --> 00:16:02,151
I'm here, why would you be lonely?

222
00:16:02,151 --> 00:16:03,786
Must you have a man to feel less lonely?

223
00:16:03,786 --> 00:16:07,056
Yeong Dal is here.
You'll have a grandchild soon.

224
00:16:07,056 --> 00:16:10,093
- Why are you lonely?
- You're still young so you don't understand.

225
00:16:10,093 --> 00:16:13,129
Having a partner is best when you're old.

226
00:16:13,129 --> 00:16:16,633
Think about it.
What if Sin Dong's mom is not around?

227
00:16:16,633 --> 00:16:18,735
And you live alone,
what will happen?

228
00:16:19,435 --> 00:16:20,837
You've been doing well all along.

229
00:16:20,837 --> 00:16:23,640
I was just pretending.

230
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:25,742
Even if I'm suffering inside,

231
00:16:25,742 --> 00:16:28,311
I still laugh.

232
00:16:29,012 --> 00:16:31,814
People told me to get married.

233
00:16:31,814 --> 00:16:35,318
But I endured it because of you.

234
00:16:35,318 --> 00:16:37,887
Both of you are married now.

235
00:16:37,887 --> 00:16:39,522
I've done everything I should do.

236
00:16:39,522 --> 00:16:42,792
Can't I have a boyfriend?

237
00:16:42,792 --> 00:16:47,230
I don't want to rely on you to live.

238
00:16:47,230 --> 00:16:53,536
Mom, I haven't forgotten.
I still remember it vividly.

239
00:16:53,536 --> 00:16:55,171
What?

240
00:16:55,171 --> 00:16:59,608
Back then, when you were running 
a beauty parlour in Myeong Dong.

241
00:16:59,608 --> 00:17:02,178
We lost the parlour because of that punk.

242
00:17:03,579 --> 00:17:08,718
Do you know how scared I was every night
thinking that you'd run away?

243
00:17:10,586 --> 00:17:13,856
I clung to your skirt while I slept.

244
00:17:13,856 --> 00:17:18,294
I was scared that you'd run away
and abandon us.

245
00:17:18,294 --> 00:17:23,199
I was 9 years old then.

246
00:17:23,199 --> 00:17:27,637
Is that so? 
You knew?

247
00:17:27,637 --> 00:17:32,542
He ran away after leaving you
with a lot of debt.

248
00:17:32,542 --> 00:17:35,345
The beauty parlour in Myong Dong was lost.

249
00:17:35,345 --> 00:17:37,914
We were chased away to live like this.
Have you forgotten?

250
00:17:42,352 --> 00:17:44,687
You can't trust any man in this world.

251
00:17:44,687 --> 00:17:47,724
They just want to use you.

252
00:17:47,724 --> 00:17:50,293
Since you have a cosmetic shop,

253
00:17:50,293 --> 00:17:54,731
that guy is just after your money.

254
00:17:54,731 --> 00:17:59,168
No, he's not.

255
00:17:59,168 --> 00:18:03,840
You still remember?
Oh my god.

256
00:18:05,942 --> 00:18:11,781
But I never once thought of abandoning you.

257
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:16,919
Because you have 2 children,

258
00:18:16,919 --> 00:18:21,124
that fellow kept on tormenting you.

259
00:18:21,124 --> 00:18:22,759
